        o/p:    Student 1 secret: hidden info
                Student 2 secret: hidden info
    
    - Explanation ✅
        A WeakMap does not allow iteration.
        Outside code can not "discover" what objects are stored inside a WeakMap(id).
        To get the secret, you need the this reference that was used in the constructor.
        External code has access to student1 and id, but not to the this reference inside myMap, unless
        you explicitly expose it, like via getSecret(), the secret value is unreachable.


#) Privacy:
    - WeakMap was intentionally designed for privacy: you can set, get, has, and delete using an object
        key, but not inspect what is inside.
    - This was a great tool for simulating private properties in JavaScript classes (before #private
        fields were added to the language).